  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Ezekiel 22:13-16",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Ezekiel 22:13-16",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Therefore I have smitten my hand at thy dishonest gain,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " &c. — Therefore I have expressed my indignation against thy avarice and unjust practices: I have called for punishment to come upon thee, and have animated and encouraged thy enemies to destroy thee. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Can thy heart endure? — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Will not thy heart fail thee when thou shalt fall into those calamities which I will certainly bring upon thee? ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And will consume thy filthiness out of thee ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Will purge thee in the furnace of afflictions, and take that method to consume thy dross, and put an end to thy idolatrous practices. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And thou shalt take thine inheritance in thyself in the sight of the heathen — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "“Instead of being mine inheritance, and under my peculiar care and protection, thou shalt be cast out among the heathen, and there eat the fruit of thine own ways, and receive the just reward of thy wickedness.” The translation of this clause in the margin seems preferable: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Thou shalt be profaned, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that is, thou shalt no longer enjoy the privileges of a city called by my name, and set apart for my worship, but shalt be laid open as common ground to be profaned by infidels: compare ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 47:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "22:1-16 The prophet is to judge the bloody city; the city of bloods. Jerusalem is so called, because of her crimes. The sins which Jerusalem stands charged with, are exceeding sinful. Murder, idolatry, disobedience to parents, oppression and extortion, profanation of the sabbath and holy things, seventh commandment sins, lewdness and adultery. Unmindfulness of God was at the bottom of all this wickedness. Sinners provoke God because they forget him. Jerusalem has filled the measure of her sins. Those who give up themselves to be ruled by their lusts, will justly be given up to be portioned by them. Those who resolve to be their own masters, let them expect no other happiness than their own hands can furnish; and a miserable portion it will prove.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
