  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Behold, therefore, I have smitten mine hand at thy dishonest gain which thou hast made,.... As one amazed at it; or as filled with indignation against it; or as grieved and distressed at it; so Jarchi and Kimchi: or else as rejoicing at the punishment going to be inflicted on them for it. So the Septuagint renders it, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"I will bring my hand upon them;'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the Targum, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"behold, I will bring my vengeance upon thee for the sins of mammon, &c. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Jarchi and Kimchi observe from their Rabbins, that four and twenty sins are recited by Ezekiel; but the final sentence of punishment is for rapine or dishonest gain, which is the greatest evil of all, 1 Timothy 6:10, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Jarchi and Kimchi observe from their Rabbins, that four and twenty sins are recited by Ezekiel; but the final sentence of punishment is for rapine or dishonest gain, which is the greatest evil of all, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Timothy 6:10",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and at thy blood which hath been in the midst of thee; the innocent blood shed in the midst of her; not so much by thieves and cutthroats, as under a pretence of justice which was very abominable indeed; against which the Lord expresses just and strong resentment. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and at thy blood which hath been in the midst of thee; the innocent blood shed in the midst of her; not so much by thieves and cutthroats, as under a pretence of justice which was very abominable indeed; against which the Lord expresses just and strong resentment. ",
            "children": []
          },
